ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: During the past 4 months on average, how frequently have you been in contact with this person?
Notes: 1=Once in the past four months; 2=Less then monthly; 3=About once a month; 4=Every other week; 5=Once or twice a week; 6=Three to six times a week; 7=Daily

ElementDescription: How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Face to face meetings
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Audio phone calls
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Video phone calls (FaceTime, Google Meet, etc.)
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Text messages
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Direct messages (DMs) on social media (no picture)
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Picture messages on social media (Snapchat, BeReal,etc)
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Commenting/replying on social media
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Emails
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Letter/mail
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? I am not frequently in contact with this person every month
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Video games with audio
How are you most frequently in contact with this person? Video games chat/text only
How important has this person been to you?
Notes: 1=Not at all Important; 2=Not very Important; 3=Somewhat Important; 4=Important; 5=Very Important; 6=Extremely Important

ElementDescription: To what extent is this person generally supportive of you, by being sensitive to your personal needs, helping you to think about things, solve problems, and by giving you the moral support you need?
Notes: 1=Not at all supportive; 2=Not very supportive; 3=Somewhat supportive; 4=Supportive; 5=Very supportive; 6=Extremely supportive

ElementDescription: Drinking status of this person
Notes: 1=Recovering alcoholic or drug user; 2=Abstainer;  3=Light drinker or user; 4=Moderate drinker or user; 5=Heavy drinker or user; 8=Don't know

ElementDescription: How often does this person drink alcohol ?
Notes: 0=Not in the past four months; 1=Once in the past four months; 2=Less often than monthly;  3=About once a month; 4=About every other week; 5=One or two times a week; 6=Three to six times a week; 7=Daily; 8=Don't know

ElementDescription: How HAS this person reacted to your drinking (or How WOULD this person react to your drinking)?
Notes: 1=Left or made you leave when you are drinking or using drugs; 2=Did not accept; 3=Neutral; 4=Accepted; 5=Encouraged; 8=Don't know

ElementDescription: How would this person react if you reduced your drinking?
Notes: 1=Strongly opposes it; 2=Opposes it; 3=Mixed; 4=Neutral; 5=Supports it; 6=Strongly supports it; 8=Don't know how they would feel about it
